## 📜 **Historical Timeline of Black-Owned Banks**

📍 **1865** – _Freedman’s Savings Bank_ established by Congress to help formerly enslaved people but collapses in 1874 due to mismanagement.  
📍 **1888** – _Capital Savings Bank_ (Washington, D.C.) becomes the first Black-owned bank chartered in the U.S.  
📍 **1903** – _True Reformers Bank_ (Virginia) is the first Black-owned bank **founded and run by African Americans**.  
📍 **1921** – _Black Wall Street (Tulsa, OK)_ thrives with Black financial institutions before its destruction.  
📍 **1934** – _Citizens Trust Bank_ (Atlanta) is founded, now one of the oldest surviving Black-owned banks.  
📍 **1960s-70s** – Civil Rights-era financial activism strengthens **Black banking movements**.  
📍 **2010s-Present** – Digital banking and **fintech solutions like Greenwood Bank** emerge to serve Black communities.

